<br>
Well, each class has some quest armor items that demonstrate real suckage as well as some great pieces. But when I had a chance to chat with a good druid friend in full Nature Walker's my opinion has changed greatly (I don't claim to know much about any class gear but druid's). While she has some good supplemental items and she looks great, her AC self-buffed is 817. Mine is 938 with 201 wis. I have only one quested peice of armor (the bracer, which along with the BP, and maybe the legs are the only things worth pursuing, IMHO) She has wisdom out the wazoo, which we all know is meaningless above the max of 200. Her resists self-buffed are not higher than mine, either.<br>
<br>
It seems that the &quot;uberousity&quot; factor of Velious quest armor should be relegated to that of getting a set of gear that actually matches. The best statistical advantages are to be found in thinking carefully abut attaining particular items that you know will demonstrate the higher advantage. And quest armor for druids in and of itself is definately not it.<br>
<br>
I suggest that anyone with bean-counting tendencies (like me) check out the total spectrum of items available for their class and see how they stack up in terms of availability and stats. I bet you will be surprised at what kind of set you can build without assuming the quested or ultra-mob gear is by default the best you can get.<br>
<br>
Die well,<br>
Aravail<br>
<br>
